title: fanoutqa: Among the Ivy League universities, which four have the lowest endowments and how many Nobel laureates do each of them have? (c70f85b1315be7ed)

chat_history.content: Among the Ivy League universities, which four have the lowest endowments and how many Nobel laureates do each of them have?

Here are the Ivy League universities with the lowest endowments, along with the number of Nobel laureates associated with each university:

1. Brown University: $4.7 billion endowment. Brown has 6 Nobel laureates among its alumni, faculty, and researchers.

2. Dartmouth College: $7.7 billion endowment. Dartmouth has 5 Nobel laureates connected to the university.

3. Cornell University: $12.7 billion endowment. Cornell boasts 45 Nobel laureates affiliated with the institution.

4. University of Pennsylvania (Penn): $17.0 billion endowment. Penn has produced or been affiliated with 33 Nobel laureates.

Note that endowment rankings can fluctuate over time due to various factors, including market performance and fundraising efforts, so these rankings may change in the future.

functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.
